# Deploy Custom Docker Image on AWS EC2 Using Docker Hub

This project demonstrates how to create a custom Docker image inside an AWS EC2 instance, push it to Docker Hub, and then pull and run the image on another EC2 instance.

## Architecture Overview

1. Create the first EC2 instance.
2. Install Docker on the EC2 instance.
3. Create and customize an Ubuntu Docker container.
4. Install required software and create files inside the container.
5. Commit the container as a new Docker image.
6. Push the image to Docker Hub.
7. Create a second EC2 instance.
8. Pull the Docker image from Docker Hub.
9. Run the image and verify the installed software and files.

